{"id":"6994","name":"bright-early-hanging-on-edition","title":"Bright &amp; Early: Hanging On Edition","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2011-04-28T09:30:00-05:00","tags":["greyhound","mnpd","nashville flood","nashville predators","nfl lockout","opryland hotel","preds","severe weather","shrek","teachers unions","tennessee state house","tennessee state senate","tornadoes","tuscaloosa","vancouver canucks","western conference semifinals"],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/39296163@N08/5654036522/in/pool-715021@N24/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\"><img src=\"http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5305/5654036522_3c4cb050e4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"334\"></a></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Good morning, Nashville. <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/story/14531164/storm-death-toll-jumps-to-178-in-south\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Yesterday&#x2019;s storms left at least 178 people dead across the states of Tennessee, Alabama, Mississippi, Georgia and Virginia</a>. Alabama took the largest beating with 128 fatalities and hundreds of injuries as the tornado <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/TORNADOHUNT/status/63444687847043072\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;twitter.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">originated in Tuscaloosa and then plowed through several other states</a>. Tennessee saw 15 dead, mainly in the southeast part of the state, and <a href=\"http://www.wsmv.com/news/27697740/detail.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wsmv.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">parts of Middle Tennessee did see some flooding</a>. Currently the storm system is still spawning tornadoes in Maryland and Virginia as it makes its way off the coast. If you&#x2019;d like to donate $10 to the Red Cross Disaster Relief Fund, just text &#x2018;REDCROSS&#x2019; to 90999,</p><ul><li><strong>Teachers union bill update. </strong><a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20110428/NEWS/304280042/2275/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">The Tennessee House and Senate are nearing an agreement that will repeal the 1978 law that allowed teachers to unionize and negotiate contracts</a>. Though they&#x2019;re still working out the language, Republican leaders are &#x201C;confident they have a final agreement.&#x201D;</li><li><strong>Show us your fang fingers. </strong>Tonight, the Preds will take on the Vancouver Canucks in Vancouver for Game 1 of the Western Conference Semifinals. They&#x2019;ll play Game 2 in Vancouver on Saturday before returning to Smashville next Tuesday and Thursday, <a href=\"http://www.ticketmaster.com/Nashville-Predators-tickets/artist/805978\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.ticketmaster.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">and there are still tickets left</a>!</li><li><strong>Bits &amp; pieces. </strong><a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20110427/NEWS01/110427009/2275/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">The Greyhound bus station will soon have a new home at Fifth and Lafayette</a>, slated to open this fall &#x2026; Mayor Dean gave the State of Metro address yesterday, but everyone was paying attention to the storms instead. <a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/city-news/dean-praises-city-employees-vows-schools-be-fully-funded-state-metro-address?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+NashvilleCityPaper-CityNews+%28Nashville+City+Paper+-+City+News%29&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Here&#x2019;s what he said</a> &#x2026; <a href=\"http://www.newschannel5.com/story/14529007/judge-denies-nfl-request-to-freeze-lockout-ruling\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.newschannel5.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">A US District Judge has denied the NFL&#x2019;s request to freeze her previous ruling to lift the lockout</a> &#x2026; For some reason, <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20110428/BUSINESS/304280044/2275/rss05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Shrek will be at the Opryland Hotel soon</a> &#x2026; <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20110428/NEWS01/304280043/2275/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Nearly 100 police officers and several civilians were honored yesterday for their heroic efforts during last year&#x2019;s flood</a>.</li></ul><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Photo by </em><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/39296163@N08/5654036522/in/pool-715021@N24/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Paul Beavers</em></a>.</p><p>No related posts.</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}